<p><span style="text-align: left;">To access your BYU-Idaho email (whether employee or student), simply login to </span><a href="http://my.byui.edu/" style="text-align: left;">my.byui.edu</a><span style="text-align: left;"> then click the Email tab.</span></p>
<p><span style="text-align: left;">Watch for more details on our planned upgrade to Microsoft Office 365 for both employees and students coming in 2013. &nbsp;Along with virtually anywhere access to familiar Office tools, plus enterprise-grade email, conferencing, and more here are just some of the advantages we'll see when we begin using Office 365:</span></p>
<ul>
<li>Access to files, documents and photos across multiple devices from anywhere.</li>
<li><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">25 GB Mailboxes</span></li>
<li>7 GB SkyDrive folders</li>
<li>Office 2013 Professional Plus (up to 5 devices/user)</li>
<li>Office Web Apps provides online access to basic versions of 4 Office applications:<ol>
<li><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Word</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Excel</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">PowerPoint</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">OneNote</span></li>
</ol></li>
<li><a href="http://lync.microsoft.com/en-us/Pages/unified-communications.aspx">Lync</a>&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Voice&nbsp;conferencing</li>
<li>Video conferencing</li>
<li>IM</li>
<li>Skype contacts right from Lync and vice versa</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Problems ? : If you experience issues of your password not working on all campus systems, such as printing or at outlook.com. Your passwords may simply be out of sync. Use the following link to&nbsp;<a href="https://web.byui.edu/Username" target="_parent">reset your password</a>.</p>
<p>Need more help? &nbsp;Here's some options:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Click </strong>the links to the left to find more information.</li>
<li><strong>Contact&nbsp;<a href="mailto:helpdesk@byui.edu" style="outline: #000000; cursor: pointer; font-weight: normal;">HelpDesk@byui.edu</a></strong> with your specific request for help with email issues. &nbsp;<br />We'll either point you to the right article or create one for you and future users to enjoy.</li>
